{# Mid-run vote-intention probe. Asks the agent "if elections were today,
   who would you vote for?" The answer is appended to the memory_stream as
   an explicit belief-state checkpoint, so subsequent events update from
   this stated intention rather than re-deriving from a frozen self_prompt.

   Counters the anchoring problem identified in distributional_analysis.md:
   without an explicit mid-run probe, every event is a noisy paragraph the
   LLM has to integrate from scratch at final-vote time, and the persona's
   coherent identity narrative dominates. With a probe, the agent has WRITTEN
   their current lean into memory — that becomes load-bearing context. #}

{% if reflections -%}
Looking back over the past months, this is what stuck with you:

{% for r in reflections -%}
[{{ r.timestamp }}] {{ r.content }}

{% endfor %}
{% endif -%}
{% if recent_memories -%}
And these are recent things still on your mind:

{% for m in recent_memories -%}
[{{ m.timestamp }}] {{ m.content }}

{% endfor %}
{% endif -%}

It is **{{ probe_date }}**. A friend asks you bluntly:

> "Forget who you voted for in 2019 for a moment. **If a state election were
> held today, which party would you vote for?** And honestly — has anything
> changed your mind since 2019, or are you still where you started?"

You haven't seen the actual ballot or candidate names yet — this is a gut
check on which **party** currently feels closest to your situation based on
what you've actually lived through. Be honest. If your views have shifted
even a little, say so. If you're conflicted between two parties, name the
one you'd lean toward.

Output ONLY a JSON object:

```json
{
  "current_lean": "BJP" | "AITC" | "INC" | "LF" | "Other",
  "drift_since_2019": "<short phrase, e.g., 'no shift', 'softening from BJP
                        toward TMC', 'leaving Left for AITC', 'gradually
                        warming to BJP', etc.>",
  "explanation": "<1-2 first-person sentences explaining WHY — what
                   specifically about the past months has confirmed or
                   shifted your view>"
}
```
